I went in for a T-Mobile Tuesday redemption for a free latte. The terms and conditions cleared stated i had until 4/16/19 to redeem with 5 days left on the offer. The cashier mentioned it to the supervisor several customers were asking for the same promotion, and they stated it was only on tuesday. After explaining it to them and showing them the app themselves the supervisor asked another employee who stated they could not fufill my offer because it was only available on Tuesdays. The offer was only available to get on Tuesdays but it allows you to use once until expiration. They were not trying to understand claiming an email told them only Tuesdays. I wanted a coffee irregardless however the way they handle that was horrible. If multiple people are asking for the same thing and by promotion it states they can receive it, what is the problem. That is poor customer service on there part and they need better communication on their knowledge on current offers. I can only imagine how many customers they refused this promotion they were entitled too. So after i purchased a coffee when it was supposed to be free i received some glares as if I was a trouble. Certain cashiers are awesome and i blame the leadership of the branch.
